    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA model ensemble meets all pre-established acceptance criteria for the three primary QoIs under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is acknowledged and accepted given that ASTM F1717 specifies a single standard test configuration, inter-laboratory agreement is excellent (CV 1.4%), and the remaining factors provide sufficient confidence for a medium-risk regulatory decision. Overall credibility is sufficient for the intended COU.",
